    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - 2000, 4000, 8000 - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>TILT</title>
            <para>The steering column assembly has four positions allowing adjustment toward or away from the driver in
                7 degree increments through a 21 degree range. The tilt/telescoping lever is located on the left side of
                the column (
                <hotlnk document="s05012_1.xml" xrefid="f0501201">Figure 1</hotlnk>). To tilt the column, pull the lever
                up and move the steering wheel to the desired position. Release the lever to lock the column in
                position.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
